main.name: Gimbal, Gremlin Prodigy
main.oracle_text:
Artifact creatures you control have trample.
At the beginning of your end step, create a 0/0 red Gremlin artifact creature token. Put X +1/+1 counters on it, where X is the number of differently named artifact tokens you control.
main.flavor_text: You are what you eat, and everything he'd eaten was brilliant.

card.name: Ichor Elixir
card.oracle_text:
If you would roll one or more planar dice, instead roll that many planar dice plus one and ignore one.
{T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: The corrupted essence of Kaldheim's World Tree became the seed from which New Phyrexia's Realmbreaker grew.

card.name: Pain Distributor
card.oracle_text:
Menace
Whenever a player casts their first spell each turn, they create a Treasure token.
Whenever an artifact an opponent controls is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, Pain Distributor deals 1 damage to that player.

card.name: Hedron Detonator
card.oracle_text:
Whenever an artifact you control enters, Hedron Detonator deals 1 damage to target opponent.
{T}, Sacrifice two artifacts: Exile the top card of your library. You may play that card this turn.
card.flavor_text: "*Compleat* this!"

card.name: Sandsteppe War Riders
card.oracle_text:
Trample
At the beginning of combat on your turn, bolster X, where X is the number of differently named artifact tokens you control. (Choose a creature with the least toughness among creatures you control and put X +1/+1 counters on it.)

card.name: Schema Thief
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever Schema Thief deals combat damage to a player, create a token that's a copy of target artifact that player controls.
card.flavor_text: "An intriguing design, but it would be much better without all that oil."

card.name: Dance with Calamity
card.oracle_text: Shuffle your library. As many times as you choose, you may exile the top card of your library. If the total mana value of the cards exiled this way is 13 or less, you may cast any number of spells from among those cards without paying their mana costs.
card.flavor_text: It was just another day on Innistrad.

card.name: Cutthroat Negotiator
card.oracle_text: Parley — Whenever Cutthroat Negotiator attacks, each player reveals the top card of their library. For each nonland card revealed this way, you create a tapped Treasure token. Then each player draws a card.
card.flavor_text: "Either you two figure out how to share, or I'm going to share these swords with the insides of your skulls."

card.name: Path of the Animist
card.oracle_text:
Search your library for up to two basic land cards, put them onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.
Will of the Planeswalkers — Starting with you, each player votes for planeswalk or chaos. If planeswalk gets more votes, planeswalk. If chaos gets more votes or the vote is tied, chaos ensues.

card.name: Brass's Bounty
card.oracle_text: For each land you control, create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
card.flavor_text:
"Why squabble for trinkets when we could be living large off all this gold?"
—Admiral Beckett Brass

card.name: Thopter Spy Network
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, if you control an artifact, create a 1/1 colorless Thopter artifact creature token with flying.
Whenever one or more artifact creatures you control deal combat damage to a player, draw a card.

card.name: Spell Swindle
card.oracle_text: Counter target spell. Create X Treasure tokens, where X is that spell's mana value. (They're artifacts with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")

card.name: Whirler Rogue
card.oracle_text:
When Whirler Rogue enters, create two 1/1 colorless Thopter artifact creature tokens with flying.
Tap two untapped artifacts you control: Target creature can't be blocked this turn.

card.name: Feldon of the Third Path
card.oracle_text: {2}{R}, {T}: Create a token that's a copy of target creature card in your graveyard, except it's an artifact in addition to its other types. It gains haste. Sacrifice it at the beginning of the next end step.
card.flavor_text: "She will come back to me."

card.name: Masterful Replication
card.oracle_text:
Choose one —

• Choose target artifact you control. Each other artifact you control becomes a copy of that artifact until end of turn.

card.oracle_text:
When Pia and Kiran Nalaar enters, create two 1/1 colorless Thopter artifact creature tokens with flying.

card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever an artifact creature you control deals combat damage to a player, you may create a 1/1 blue Thopter artifact creature token with flying.
card.flavor_text: Whether mechanical or biological, life finds a way to propagate itself.

card.oracle_text:
Choose one or both —
• Create a token that's a copy of target artifact.
• Create a token that's a copy of target creature, except it's an artifact in addition to its other types.
card.flavor_text: "From the first touch, I know exactly what the metal wants to be."

card.name: Crack Open
card.oracle_text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment. Create a Treasure token. (It's an artifact with "{T}, Sacrifice this artifact: Add one mana of any color.")
card.flavor_text: What no spell or lockpick could open, the forest coaxed apart.

Creature tokens you control have flying.

card.name: Reality Shift
card.oracle_text: Exile target creature. Its controller manifests the top card of their library. (That player puts the top card of their library onto the battlefield face down as a 2/2 creature. If it's a creature card, it can be turned face up any time for its mana cost.)

card.name: Root Out
card.oracle_text:
Destroy target artifact or enchantment.

card.oracle_text: If you would create a Clue, Food, or Treasure token, instead create one of each.
card.flavor_text: Automated systems at the Tolarian Academy sort new acquisitions for optimal use, determining which should be studied, eaten, or sold.

Flying

card.flavor_text: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

card.name: Game Trail

card.flavor_text: Only one vault was great enough to hold Emrakul.
